textAfterTable: Mtl: Fiberglass LOD: 36'9" / 15.849m Deck: Fiberglass Beam: 20'2" / 6.146m Top: Sloop Rig Min Draft: 3'4 / 1.016m Naval Arch: Van Peteghem & Lauriot-Prevost Max Draft: 3'4 / 1.016m Engines: Twin x 25/hp Diesels IB Perkins Headroom: 6'3 / 1.92m Accom-Gsts: 3 staterooms Flag: USA Galley: Down Sail Area: 839sqft / 77.945sqm Crew-Accom: 2 berth Equipped: For Cruising      If the exterior of this Lagoon 37 is too spacey for you, you are definitely going to have trouble with her interior as well. Not only is the expanse of space quite unfamiliar to a sailor accustomed to that of mono-hulls; but also Lagoon's style of interior finishing and decorating is far from traditional as well. Her configuration consists of a Salon on the centerline with access to hulls that are equipped with (2) berths port and (2) starboards, a chart table, a fully-kitted galley and (2) head/showers.
